.TH "ata_dev_revalidate" 9 "ata_dev_revalidate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_dev_revalidate \- Revalidate ATA device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_dev_revalidate
.BI "(struct ata_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int new_class "  ","
.BI "unsigned int readid_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to revalidate
.IP "new_class" 12
new class code
.IP "readid_flags" 12
read ID flags

Re-read IDENTIFY page, make sure \fIdev\fP is still attached to the
port and reconfigure it according to the new IDENTIFY page.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep)
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno otherwise
